In battle, this Pokémon swings around two thick vines. If these vines slammed into a 10-story building, they could easily topple it.
This colossal, flame-winged figure of a Charizard was brought about by Gigantamax energy.
It’s not very good at precision shooting. When attacking, it just fires its 31 cannons over and over and over.
Crystallized Gigantamax energy makes up this Pokémon’s blindingly bright and highly toxic scales.
Its Gigantamax power expanded, forming its supersized body and towering tail.
The pattern that has appeared on its giant coin is thought to be the key to unlocking the secrets of the Dynamax phenomenon.
The Gigantamax energy coursing through its arms makes its punches hit as hard as bomb blasts.
Rumor has it that its gigantic mouth leads not into its body, filled with cursed energy, but instead directly to the afterlife.
The flow of Gigantamax energy has spurred this Pokémon’s left pincer to grow to an enormous size. That claw can pulverize anything.
Over 5,000 people can ride on its shell at once. And it’s a very comfortable ride, without the slightest shaking or swaying.
Gigantamax energy upped the fluffiness of the fur around Eevee’s neck. The fur will envelop a foe, capturing its body and captivating its mind.
Gigantamax energy has affected stray seeds and even pebbles that got stuck to Snorlax, making them grow to a huge size.
Due to Gigantamax energy, this Pokémon’s toxic gas has become much thicker, congealing into masses shaped like discarded toys.
In a distant land, there are legends about a cyclopean giant. In fact, the giant was a Melmetal that was flooded with Gigantamax energy.
Gigantamax energy has caused Rillaboom’s stump to grow into a drum set that resembles a forest.
Infused with Cinderace’s fighting spirit, the gigantic Pyro Ball never misses its targets and completely roasts opponents.
Gigantamax Inteleon’s Water Gun move fires at Mach 7. As the Pokémon takes aim, it uses the crest on its head to gauge wind and temperature.
Imbued with Gigantamax energy, its wings can whip up winds more forceful than any a hurricane could muster. The gusts blow everything away.
Its brain has grown to a gargantuan size, as has the rest of its body. This Pokémon’s intellect and psychic abilities are overpowering.
It responded to Gigantamax energy by becoming bipedal. First it comes crashing down on foes, and then it finishes them off with its massive jaws.
Its body is a colossal stove. With Gigantamax energy stoking the fire, this Pokémon’s flame burns hotter than 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
Under the influence of Gigantamax energy, it produces much more sweet nectar, and its shape has changed to resemble a giant apple.
It blasts its opponents with massive amounts of sweet, sticky nectar, drowning them under the deluge.
Its sand pouch has grown to tremendous proportions. More than 1,000,000 tons of sand now swirl around its body.
Its excessive electric energy is its weapon. This Pokémon can build up more electricity than any thundercloud.
Its excessive electric energy is its weapon. This Pokémon can build up more electricity than any thundercloud.
Gigantamax energy has evoked a rise in its body temperature, now reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. Its heat waves incinerate its enemies.
This Pokémon can read the emotions of creatures over 30 miles away. The minute it senses hostility, it goes on the attack.
By transforming its leg hair, this Pokémon delivers power-packed drill kicks that can bore huge holes in Galar’s terrain.
Cream pours endlessly from this Pokémon’s body. The cream stiffens when compressed by an impact. A harder impact results in harder cream.
So much power is packed within its trunk that if it were to unleash that power, the resulting blast could level mountains and change the landscape.
It’s grown to resemble a skyscraper. Parts of its towering body glow due to a profusion of energy.
People call it the embodiment of rage. It’s said that this Pokémon’s terrifying expression and shout will rid the world of malevolence.
As it waits for the right moment to unleash its Gigantamax power, this Pokémon maintains a perfect one-legged stance. It won’t even twitch.

¡Hola, %PLAYERNAME%! ¡Qué suerte tenemos! Es increíble ver tantos Popplio en un mismo lugar.
Escuché que estos Pokémon tienen una gran fuerza de voluntad y pueden inflar globos con la nariz. ¡Fascinante!
Practican sin descanso para poder aprender a inflar globos cada vez más grandes.
Estudiar al Pokémon León Marino va a ser todo un espectáculo. ¿Por qué no atrapas uno para ver esas habilidades en primera persona?
¡Fantástico, %PLAYERNAME%! Me alegra saber que las acrobacias de Popplio no te desanimaron.
¿Sabías que no infla esos globos solamente para mostrar su destreza?
En el combate, los globos pueden herir a los rivales al explotar.
Y el encanto de Popplio no termina aquí. ¡Intenta evolucionar a tu Popplio a Brionne y verás a lo que me refiero!
¡Lo lograste, %PLAYERNAME%! Tu Brionne tiene una gran presencia escénica. ¡Nació para ser artista!
Seguro que Brionne será un compañero realmente entretenido. Escuché que este Pokémon no duda en ponerse a bailar para animar a su Entrenador cuando se siente mal.
Parece que tu Brionne está listo para llevar su talento al siguiente nivel. ¡Hagamos que este bailarín evolucione a Primarina!
¡Bravo, %PLAYERNAME%! Qué Primarina más espectacular. Este Pokémon tiene el sobrenombre de Diva, y le da el golpe de gracia a su presa con un canto y baile que derrochan elegancia.
¡Me abruma su deslumbrante apariencia! ¿Crees que me daría un autógrafo?
Gracias por ayudarme a no perder el compás con mi investigación hoy. Espero que Primarina y tú tengan un día realmente espectacular.
¡Estoy deseando ver lo lejos que puede llegar su carrera tanto encima como debajo del escenario de los combates!

Esta Investigación Temporal, que te desafía a explorar y completar tareas de Investigación de Campo, lleva a encuentros con los siguientes Pokémon: ¡Aerodactyl, Cranidos, Shieldon, Tirtouga, Archen, Tyrunt y Amaura! Durante el evento, los Pokémon que te encuentres en esta Investigación Temporal tienen la misma probabilidad de ser brillantes que los que eclosionen de Huevos, los que te encuentres en estado salvaje o aquellos que te encuentres en las Investigaciones de Campo. Las recompensas incluyen lo siguiente: • 2 Incubadoras y 1 Superincubadora.
Las recompensas incluyen lo siguiente: • Artículos prémium dentro del juego, como Caramelos Raros y Ultrabolas, entre otros • Encuentros adicionales con Beldum y sus evoluciones

¡Esta entrada tiene como objetivo ayudarte a convertirte en la persona que mejor combate dándote la oportunidad de atrapar Pokémon populares en la Liga de Combates GO! Las recompensas incluyen: • Encuentros con Lickitung, Lanturn, Azumarill, Skarmory, Vigoroth, Cresselia, Stunfisk de Galar, Carbink y Charjabug • 25,000 Polvos Estrella y 1 Pase de Combate Prémium
